15024 /* ignore JIS X 0201 latin */

15039 static VALUE
15040 fun_si_iso2022jp_kddi_decoder(void *statep, const unsigned char *s, size_t l)
15041 {
15042     unsigned char *sp = statep;
15043     if (*sp == G0_ASCII)
15044         return (VALUE)NOMAP;
15045     else if (0x21 <= s[0] && s[0] <= 0x7e)
15046         return (VALUE)iso2022jp_kddi_decoder_jisx0208_rest;
15047     else
15048         return (VALUE)INVALID;

15051 static ssize_t
15052 fun_so_iso2022jp_kddi_decoder(void *statep, const unsigned char *s, size_t l, unsigned char *o, size_t osize)
15053 {
15054     unsigned char *sp = statep;
15055     if (s[0] == 0x1b) {
15056         if (s[1] == '(') {
15057             switch (s[l-1]) {
15058               case 'B': /* US-ASCII */
15059               case 'J': /* JIS X 0201 Roman */
15060                 *sp = G0_ASCII;
15061                 break;
15062             }
15063         }
15064         else {
15065             switch (s[l-1]) {
15066               case '@':
15067                 *sp = G0_JISX0208_1978;
15068                 break;
15069 
15070               case 'B':
15071                 *sp = G0_JISX0208_1983;
15072                 break;
15073             }
15074         }
15075         return 0;
15076     }
15077     else {
15078         if (*sp == G0_JISX0208_1978)
15079             o[0] = EMACS_MULE_LEADING_CODE_JISX0208_1978;
15080         else
15081             o[0] = EMACS_MULE_LEADING_CODE_JISX0208_1983;
15082         o[1] = s[0] | 0x80;
15083         o[2] = s[1] | 0x80;
15084         return 3;
15085     }
15086 }

15100 static ssize_t
15101 fun_so_iso2022jp_kddi_encoder(void *statep, const unsigned char *s, size_t l, unsigned char *o, size_t osize)
15102 {
15103     unsigned char *sp = statep;
15104     unsigned char *output0 = o;
15105     int newstate;
15106 
15107     if (l == 1)
15108         newstate = G0_ASCII;
15109     else if (s[0] == EMACS_MULE_LEADING_CODE_JISX0208_1978)
15110         newstate = G0_JISX0208_1978;
15111     else
15112         newstate = G0_JISX0208_1983;
15113 
15114     if (*sp != newstate) {
15115         *o++ = 0x1b;
15116         switch (newstate) {
15117           case G0_ASCII:
15118             *o++ = '(';
15119             *o++ = 'B';
15120             break;
15121           case G0_JISX0208_1978:
15122             *o++ = '$';
15123             *o++ = '@';
15124             break;
15125           default:
15126             *o++ = '$';
15127             *o++ = 'B';
15128             break;
15129         }
15130         *sp = newstate;
15131     }
15132 
15133     if (l == 1) {
15134         *o++ = s[0] & 0x7f;
15135     }
15136     else {
15137         *o++ = s[1] & 0x7f;
15138         *o++ = s[2] & 0x7f;
15139     }
15140 
15141     return o - output0;
15142 }

15153 finish_iso2022jp_kddi_encoder(void *statep, unsigned char *o, size_t osize)
15154 {
15155     unsigned char *sp = statep;
15156     unsigned char *output0 = o;
15157

15163     *o++ = 'B';
